lead_paragraph: Preliminary results released Saturday showed that reformist and moderate candidates were leading in one of the two elections just held by Iran, state news media quoted the Interior Ministry as saying.

headline.print_headline: Early Election Results Favor Reformists in Iran
headline.main: Early Results Show Reformists and Moderates Drawing Votes in Iran Elections

snippet: Preliminary results released Saturday showed that reformist and moderate candidates were leading in one of the two elections just held by Iran, state news media quoted the Interior Ministry as saying.
abstract: Parliamentary elections in Iran appear to have resulted in significant gains for moderate candidates, according to country's Interior Ministry; vote is first to be held following contentious international nuclear agreement, which was opposed by hard-line leaders.
